---

## BACKUP EXECUTION COMMANDS

### Recommended Method (Supabase CLI):
```bash
# Login
supabase login

# Link project
supabase link --project-ref <your-project-ref>

# Create schema backup
supabase db dump --schema-only > schema_backup_20260316.sql

# Create data backup
supabase db dump --data-only > data_backup_20260316.sql

# Verify
ls -lh schema_backup_20260316.sql data_backup_20260316.sql
```

### Alternative Method (pg_dump):
```bash
# Replace [YOUR-PASSWORD], [HOST], [PORT] with actual values
pg_dump "postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@[HOST]:[PORT]/postgres" \
  --schema-only --no-owner --no-privileges \
  > schema_backup_20260316.sql

pg_dump "postgresql://postgres:[YOUR-PASSWORD]@[HOST]:[PORT]/postgres" \
  --data-only --no-owner --no-privileges --disable-triggers \
  > data_backup_20260316.sql
```

---

## VERIFICATION CHECKLIST

Run these commands after backup:

```bash
# 1. Check files exist
test -f schema_backup_20260316.sql && echo "✅ Schema backup exists"
test -f data_backup_20260316.sql && echo "✅ Data backup exists"

# 2. Check file sizes
ls -lh schema_backup_20260316.sql data_backup_20260316.sql

# 3. Verify schema contains tables
grep "CREATE TABLE" schema_backup_20260316.sql | wc -l
# Should show 10+ tables

# 4. Verify commission tables present
grep -E "CREATE TABLE.*commissions_" schema_backup_20260316.sql
# Should show:
# - commissions_waterfall
# - commissions_overrides
# - commissions_cabs
# - commissions_bonuses
# - commissions_runs
# - commissions_payouts

# 5. Verify data file has content
head -20 data_backup_20260316.sql
# Should show COPY or INSERT statements
```

